// Semantic direction:
// batch_job processes a bounded dataset; batch_checkpoint saves progress for resume on failure.
// etl_pipeline chains extract, transform, and load stages into a complete data movement workflow.
// extract_stage reads data from data_source; transform_stage reshapes it; load_stage writes to data_sink.
// read_page fetches one page of records; page_token tracks the cursor for stateless pagination.
// write_mode determines behavior on existing data: append adds, overwrite replaces, upsert updates or inserts.
// schema describes the expected structure; infer_schema derives it from a sample of source data.
// field_nullable indicates whether null values are allowed; field_default_val fills missing values.
// map_row applies a function to transform each row into a new row with different fields.
// add_computed_column derives a new field from existing columns using an expression.
// cast_column converts a field's type (e.g. text to integer) with optional parse error handling.
// group_by partitions rows by group_key for aggregation; each group produces one output row.
// agg_collect gathers all values for a key into a list.
// join_transform combines rows from two datasets matched by join_key.
// build_side is the smaller dataset loaded into memory; probe_side is scanned and matched.
// type_left_outer preserves all left rows and fills right fields with null when no match exists.
// data_quality runs quality_checks over each row; failed_rows are routed to quarantine_sink.
// check_referential verifies that a field value exists in a reference dataset.
// quality_report summarizes how many rows passed and failed each check.

// Primitive flow:
// batch_job: source_schema infer -> read_page loop:
//   extract: read_batch(source) -> raw rows
//   transform: filter_row -> map_row -> cast_column -> add_computed_column
//   aggregate (optional): group_by -> agg_sum/count/avg -> aggregated rows
//   join (optional): build_side load -> probe_side scan -> join output
//   quality_check: check_not_null + check_range -> failed_rows -> quarantine_sink
//   load: write_batch(sink, mode) -> batch_checkpoint
// resume: batch_resume reads checkpoint -> skip already-written pages

// This defines batch ETL pipelines: extract, transform, aggregate, join,
// data quality checks, and checkpointed resumable batch jobs.

