// Semantic direction:
// dist_query plans a SQL or dataframe query across multiple worker_nodes.
// dist_stage is one phase of the distributed plan; stages are connected by shuffle exchanges.
// shuffle redistributes data so all rows with the same shuffle_key land on the same partition.
// hash_partition assigns rows to partitions via hash(shuffle_key) % partition_count.
// range_partition assigns rows to partitions based on sorted value ranges for merge joins.
// shuffle_write serializes rows and sends them to target partitions; shuffle_read receives and deserializes.
// broadcast_join replicates the broadcast_dataset to every worker, avoiding shuffle for small tables.
// broadcast_threshold is the size below which a table is automatically broadcast.
// strategy_shuffle_join shuffles both tables on the join key and performs a local hash join per partition.
// strategy_sort_merge_dist sorts both sides by join key, then merges; good for pre-sorted data.
// partial_aggregate computes local aggregates per partition; final_aggregate combines them globally.
// combine_fn specifies how partial aggregates merge (e.g. sum of sums, max of maxes).
// agg_distinct_dist counts distinct values across partitions using hyperloglog (approximate) or exact deduplication.
// hyperloglog (HLL) is a space-efficient probabilistic cardinality estimator; hll_merge combines registers.
// hll_estimate returns the estimated count with configurable accuracy.
// skew occurs when a few shuffle_keys have disproportionately many rows, causing uneven load.
// salt_key appends a random suffix to skewed keys to spread load; salted_join undoes the salt before output.
// repartition redistributes data to a different partition count; coalesce_dist reduces partitions cheaply.
// all_reduce aggregates a value across all workers and returns the result to all.
// query_fragment is a unit of work assigned to one worker; it reads fragment_inputs and writes fragment_outputs.
// coordinator dispatches fragments to worker_nodes and collects fragment_results.
// stream_exchange passes rows between stages without materializing them fully.

// Primitive flow:
// dist query planning: sql_plan -> dist_stage decomposition
//   identify shuffle points: group_by keys, join keys -> insert stage_shuffle
//   small side < broadcast_threshold -> replace shuffle with broadcast_join
//   skew_detect: estimate key frequency -> skewed keys -> salt_key
// execution: coordinator dispatches fragments to workers
//   worker: local scan -> partial_aggregate -> shuffle_write (hash partition by key)
//   exchange: shuffle_read from all senders -> local hash_join or sort_merge_join
//   final_aggregate: combine partials -> global result
//   gather: final stage collects from all workers -> coordinator -> result

// This defines distributed join strategies (shuffle, broadcast, sort-merge),
// two-phase aggregation, HyperLogLog cardinality, skew mitigation, and query fragment execution.

