// Semantic direction:
// data_stdlib is the Norscode standard library for data processing: streams, batches, SQL, and more.
// dataframe is the primary in-memory table structure: a schema plus typed columns.
// df_create builds a dataframe from a list of rows; df_from_parquet reads from a Parquet file.
// df_describe returns summary statistics (count, mean, min, max, null count) per column.
// df_select projects columns; df_filter_df keeps rows matching a predicate.
// df_groupby + df_agg_df performs split-apply-combine: group rows by key, then aggregate.
// df_pivot rotates unique values of one column into separate columns.
// df_fillna replaces null values with a fill value or strategy (forward-fill, backward-fill).
// df_dropna removes rows containing at least one null value.
// df_dedup_df removes duplicate rows; df_cast_df changes a column's type.
// lazy_frame is a deferred computation plan; lf_collect triggers execution and returns a dataframe.
// lf_explain prints the query plan for inspection before executing.
// nc data run processes a dataset described by a Norscode data pipeline script.
// cmd_data_schema infers and prints the schema of a data file without loading it fully.
// cmd_data_validate checks a data file against a schema and reports violations.
// cmd_data_convert transforms between formats (CSV to Parquet, JSON to Avro).
// cmd_data_diff compares two datasets and reports added, removed, and changed rows.
// cmd_data_stats prints column statistics for quick profiling.
// pipeline_builder is the fluent API for constructing data pipelines programmatically.
// pb_branch splits one stream into multiple based on a predicate.
// pb_dry_run validates the pipeline plan without executing any I/O.
// data_test is a declarative quality assertion framework for data pipelines.
// test_freshness checks that the dataset was updated within a specified time window.
// test_duplicate_free verifies no duplicate rows exist on a key column set.
// data_test_suite groups multiple tests; data_test_report summarizes pass/fail counts.

// Primitive flow:
// dataframe: df_from_csv("data.csv") -> df_filter_df(age > 18) -> df_groupby("city")
//   -> df_agg_df(count()) -> df_sort("count", desc=true) -> df_to_parquet("output.parquet")
// lazy: lf_scan("data.parquet") -> lf_filter(col > 0) -> lf_groupby -> lf_agg -> lf_collect
//   lf_explain: print plan before collect for optimization review
// nc data run pipeline.no --input data.csv --output result.parquet
// nc data validate --schema schema.json data.parquet -> report violations
// data_test_suite: test_no_nulls(col="id") + test_freshness(max_age="1d")
//   -> run -> data_test_report: 2/2 passed or failure details

// This defines the Norscode data processing stdlib: dataframe API, lazy frames,
// CLI commands, pipeline builder, and declarative data quality testing.

