// Semantic direction:
// websocket is a full-duplex persistent connection established via an HTTP upgrade.
// ws_handshake converts an HTTP/1.1 connection into a WebSocket connection.
// sec_websocket_key is a random base64 value from the client; the server computes compute_accept_key.
// compute_accept_key concatenates the key with a magic GUID and returns SHA-1 base64 encoded.
// ws_frame is the binary framing unit: fin bit, opcode, optional masking_key, and payload.
// frame_masked is always set for client-to-server frames; servers must unmask_payload before reading.
// opcode_ping/pong implement the keep-alive mechanism; the receiver must reply to each ping with a pong.
// opcode_continuation assembles fragmented messages; fragment_complete fires when frame_fin is set.
// ws_fragment_buffer accumulates continuation frames until the final fragment arrives.
// ws_broadcast sends a message to all connected ws_connections managed by a ws_server.
// ws_room groups connections into named channels; ws_room_broadcast sends to all members of a room.
// ws_ping_interval sends periodic pings to detect dead connections without waiting for a write failure.
// ws_reconnect automatically re-establishes a dropped connection with exponential reconnect_delay.
// sse (Server-Sent Events) provides server-to-client push over a plain HTTP connection.
// sse_event is a text-format message with optional sse_id, sse_event_type, and sse_data fields.
// sse_retry tells the client how long to wait before reconnecting after a connection drop.
// last_event_id is sent by the client on reconnect so the server can resume from where it left off.
// sse_channel is a named topic; sse_publish sends an event to all subscribers of a channel.
// SSE uses a persistent HTTP GET with Content-Type text/event-stream and Transfer-Encoding chunked.

// Primitive flow:
// WebSocket server: HTTP GET with Upgrade: websocket
//   -> ws_handshake: validate sec_websocket_key -> compute_accept_key -> 101 Switching Protocols
//   -> ws_state = ws_open -> ws_on_connect callback
//   -> read loop: read ws_frame -> unmask_payload -> opcode dispatch
//      text/binary -> ws_on_message; ping -> ws_send_pong; close -> ws_send_close -> ws_closed
// Client ws_send: encode ws_frame(masked, fin=true) -> tcp_write
// SSE endpoint: HTTP GET -> response(200, Content-Type: text/event-stream, Cache-Control: no-cache)
//   -> keep connection open -> server pushes: sse_format("data: message\n\n") -> tcp_write
//   -> client EventSource parses events -> fires event listeners
// sse_channel: sse_publish("news", event) -> for each subscriber: sse_send(conn, event)

// This defines WebSocket handshake, framing, masking, ping/pong, rooms,
// reconnection, and Server-Sent Events with channels and last-event-id resumption.

