// Semantic direction:
// grpc is a high-performance RPC framework using HTTP/2 and Protocol Buffers.
// grpc_channel is a virtual connection to a gRPC endpoint; it manages the underlying HTTP/2 connection.
// channel_credentials selects TLS or insecure transport for the channel.
// service_config embeds load_balancing_policy and retry policy for the channel.
// grpc_call wraps one RPC invocation with deadline, metadata, and status.
// call_metadata carries key-value pairs analogous to HTTP headers (auth tokens, trace IDs).
// call_deadline is an absolute timestamp; the RPC is cancelled server-side if not completed in time.
// unary_call sends one request and receives one response synchronously from the caller's perspective.
// server_streaming sends one request and receives a stream of responses.
// client_streaming sends a stream of requests and receives one final response.
// bidi_streaming sends and receives streams simultaneously.
// stream_close_send signals that no more messages will be sent (half-close).
// protobuf is the binary serialization format; each message is a sequence of tagged fields.
// field_number identifies a field in the wire format; it never changes once published.
// wire_type determines how the field's bytes are interpreted: varint, fixed, or length-delimited.
// proto_sint32 uses zigzag encoding for efficient serialization of negative integers.
// proto_any carries an arbitrary message type alongside its type URL for dynamic dispatch.
// proto_timestamp and proto_duration are well-known types for time values.
// grpc_interceptor wraps calls for cross-cutting concerns: auth, logging, metrics, tracing.
// interceptor_chain applies multiple interceptors in order; each calls the next in the chain.
// grpc_reflection lets tools like grpcurl discover services and methods at runtime.
// health_check_grpc implements the standard gRPC health checking protocol.
// grpc_keepalive sends HTTP/2 pings to detect dead connections on idle channels.

// Primitive flow:
// proto_encode(message) -> for each field: tag(field_number, wire_type) + encoded value -> bytes
// proto_decode(bytes) -> parse tag -> field_number lookup -> decode by wire_type -> message
// unary call: client.stub.method(request) -> proto_encode(request)
//   -> h2_stream(path="/pkg.Service/Method") -> frame_headers + frame_data
//   -> server: proto_decode -> handler(request) -> proto_encode(response)
//   -> frame_headers(status 200, grpc-status) + frame_data
//   -> client: proto_decode -> response value
// server_streaming: same as unary but server sends multiple frame_data, then trailers
// interceptor: client_interceptor wraps call -> log + add auth metadata -> invoke next -> log result

// This defines gRPC channel setup, four RPC patterns, Protocol Buffer encoding,
// interceptors, reflection, health checking, and keepalive.

