// Semantic direction:
// test_server spins up a real HTTP server on a test_addr for integration testing.
// in_process_server avoids network syscalls by connecting test_client directly in memory.
// loopback_transport routes requests through the loopback interface for E2E testing without mocking.
// http_test_client sends requests to the test_server and provides assertion helpers.
// assert_status checks the response status code; assert_json_body parses and deep-compares JSON.
// record_request captures incoming requests for later inspection; replayed_request re-sends a captured one.
// mock_handler returns a configured mock_response; mock_delay adds artificial latency to simulate slowness.
// mock_sequence cycles through different responses in order to test retry and fallback logic.
// assert_called verifies that a mock_route received at least one request during the test.
// sim_network is a programmable virtual network for chaos testing distributed scenarios.
// sim_latency adds a fixed or normally-distributed delay to each simulated message.
// sim_jitter adds random variation to latency; sim_packet_loss drops a fraction of messages.
// sim_bandwidth limits the throughput on a sim_link.
// sim_partition creates a network split: nodes on different sides cannot communicate.
// sim_advance_time moves virtual time forward to trigger timeouts without waiting in real time.
// fault_injection_net wraps a real connection and randomly applies inject_reset, inject_corrupt, or inject_drop.
// packet_capture records raw bytes from a network interface using libpcap-style filtering.
// capture_filter is a BPF expression (e.g. "tcp port 80") that selects which packets to capture.
// pcap_file stores captured packets in the standard .pcap format for Wireshark analysis.
// net_metric instruments a connection to count bytes, packets, errors, and RTT samples.
// flow_log records summaries of network connections for security analysis and billing.
// flow_action marks whether the flow was allowed or denied by a firewall or policy engine.

// Primitive flow:
// unit test: http_test_server.start -> http_test_client.get("/path")
//   -> assert_status(200) + assert_json_body({key: value})
//   -> test_server.stop
// mock: mock_handler.add_route(GET, "/api", response=200, body="ok", delay=50ms)
//   -> client.get("/api") -> mock returns configured response
//   -> assert_called_with(GET, "/api", headers)
// chaos test: sim_network(nodes=[A,B,C], links) -> sim_latency(A->B, 100ms)
//   -> sim_partition(A, [B,C]) -> A cannot reach B/C -> test timeout handling
//   -> sim_advance_time(30s) -> timeouts fire -> assert error recovery
// capture: packet_capture(iface="lo", filter="tcp port 8080") -> .pcap file -> packet_inspect

// This defines HTTP test servers, mock handlers with assertion, network simulation
// with fault injection, packet capture, and network flow observability.

