// Semantic direction:
// input_event is the union of all user input events delivered by the OS.
// mouse_modifiers indicates which modifier keys were held during a mouse event.
// keyboard_shortcut is a key_code plus modifier combination; shortcut_match checks an event against it.
// gesture_recognizer tracks a sequence of touch events and fires a high-level gesture event.
// gesture_pinch reports the scale factor change; gesture_pan reports the translation delta.
// focus_manager tracks the currently focused_widget and moves focus on Tab key presses.
// focus_trap restricts focus to a set of widgets (used in dialog overlays).
// tab_index sets the focus traversal order; negative values exclude a widget from tab navigation.
// animation interpolates a numeric value between anim_from and anim_to over anim_duration.
// anim_easing controls the rate of change: ease_in starts slow, ease_out ends slow.
// easing_spring simulates a spring: spring_stiffness controls speed, spring_damping controls oscillation.
// anim_tick advances all active animations by one frame and fires callbacks.
// transition is a declarative animation tied to a property change: it auto-starts on value change.
// animated_value wraps a value and returns its interpolated position for the current frame.
// platform_clipboard reads and writes the OS clipboard for copy/paste operations.
// platform_file_dialog opens the native file picker; it returns selected file paths.
// platform_notifications sends system notifications visible outside the app window.
// dark_mode detects the OS appearance setting so the app can switch color themes automatically.

// Primitive flow:
// input loop: OS event -> input_event -> dispatch to focused_widget or hit_test widget
//   keyboard: shortcut_match(event, shortcuts) -> handler or focus_next/prev
//   mouse: mouse_pos -> hit_test -> on_hover + on_click
//   touch: gesture_recognizer.feed(touch_event) -> gesture_tap -> on_click
// animation: anim_start(from=0, to=1, duration=300ms, easing=ease_out)
//   each frame: anim_tick -> anim_value interpolated -> re-render widget
//   anim_complete -> callback -> remove animation
// transition: widget.opacity changes 0->1 -> transition triggers -> animated_value drives rendering
// dark_mode: detect_dark_mode -> theme.switch(dark/light) -> re-render all widgets

// This defines input handling, gesture recognition, focus management,
// spring-based animation, transitions, clipboard, file dialogs, and dark mode.

