// Semantic direction:
// wal ensures durability: every change is written to wal_file before modifying data pages.
// lsn (Log Sequence Number) uniquely identifies each wal_record position in the log stream.
// flush_lsn is the highest lsn whose bytes have been written to disk; durable_lsn is fsync-confirmed.
// wal_record carries the lsn, transaction ID, record_type, and the actual change description.
// record_prev_lsn links records within one transaction for undo traversal.
// rtype_full_page writes a complete page image when a page is modified for the first time after a checkpoint.
// rtype_compensate (CLR) is written during undo to record that an undo operation was applied.
// group_commit batches multiple transactions' flush requests into one fsync for throughput.
// wal_bg_flusher periodically flushes buffered records so the buffer does not fill between commits.
// checkpoint saves checkpoint_redo_lsn, dirty_page_table, and active_transactions.
// checkpoint_redo_lsn is the earliest lsn where redo must begin after a crash.
// dirty_page_table tracks which pages have been modified but not yet written to disk.
// recovery uses the ARIES algorithm: Analysis → Redo → Undo.
// analysis_phase scans the log from the checkpoint to reconstruct dirty_page_table and transaction_table.
// redo_phase re-applies all logged changes from recovery_lsn forward, even for loser transactions.
// undo_phase rolls back all incomplete (loser) transactions using record_prev_lsn chains.
// full_page_write ensures that partial page writes on crash do not corrupt data.
// fpw_page_image is written into the WAL before the first modification after each checkpoint.
// archive_wal copies completed wal_segments to long-term storage for point-in-time recovery.
// restore_command fetches archived segments during recovery beyond the local log.

// Primitive flow:
// write: txn begins -> rtype_begin record written
//   modify page -> if fpw_enabled and first mod since checkpoint: write rtype_full_page
//   -> write rtype_insert/update/delete record
//   commit: write rtype_commit -> flush_wal (group_commit) -> fsync -> durable_lsn updated
// checkpoint: dirty_page_table + active_txns + checkpoint_redo_lsn -> rtype_checkpoint written
//   background: checkpoint_bg runs every checkpoint_interval
// crash recovery: open wal -> find last checkpoint -> analysis -> redo(from redo_lsn) -> undo(losers)

// This defines Write-Ahead Logging: LSN tracking, record types, group commit,
// checkpointing, and the ARIES recovery algorithm (Analysis, Redo, Undo).

