// Semantic direction:
// page is the fundamental storage unit; page_size is typically 8 KB.
// page_lsn is the LSN of the most recent WAL record affecting this page.
// page_lower is the end of the item_id array; page_upper is the start of item data.
// Free space lies between page_lower and page_upper; page_free_space is their difference.
// item_id is a fixed-size slot in the item directory; item_offset points into the page body.
// item_dead marks a slot that has been logically removed but not yet compacted.
// heap_tuple stores a variable-length row with a fixed header and variable attribute data.
// tuple_null_bitmap is a bit array marking which attributes are NULL.
// page_compact reorganizes a page to consolidate free space after deletions.
// buffer_pool is the shared memory region holding cached disk pages.
// buf_descriptor records the state of one buffer: which page it holds, refcount, and dirty flag.
// buf_tag identifies a page by relation_oid, fork, and page_id.
// buf_pin increases refcount; buf_unpin decreases it; a page with refcount > 0 cannot be evicted.
// buf_dirty marks a page as modified; buf_flush writes it to disk and clears the flag.
// clock_sweep is the buffer eviction policy: a hand moves through descriptors evicting unpinned pages.
// buf_usage_count is decremented each clock pass; eviction happens when usage_count reaches zero.
// tablespace maps a logical oid to a filesystem directory.
// relation_fork separates the main data file from the free_space_map and visibility_map files.
// free_space_map records approximately how much free space each page has for tuple insertion.
// visibility_map tracks pages where all tuples are visible to all transactions (vm_all_visible).
// vm_all_frozen marks pages where all tuples are frozen, allowing VACUUM to skip them.

// Primitive flow:
// read page: buf_pool lookup by buf_tag -> hit: buf_pin -> return buf
//   miss: buf_evict (clock_sweep, find buf_usage_count==0 and not dirty or flush first)
//   -> page_read from disk -> buf_pin -> return
// write tuple: page_alloc from fsm_search(free_space_needed)
//   -> page_add_item(tuple) -> buf_mark_dirty -> update page_lsn = current_lsn
// eviction: clock_hand advances -> buf_usage_count-- -> if 0 and not pinned -> buf_evict
//   dirty: buf_flush (write to disk, fsync if checkpoint) -> buf_evict

// This defines page layout, item slots, heap tuple format, buffer pool
// management with clock-sweep eviction, tablespaces, and the free space map.

