// Semantic direction:
// builtin_registry maps builtin_id to the native Norscode/Python function that implements it.
// call_builtin looks up the builtin_fn by builtin_id, validates arity, and invokes it.
// builtin_varargs means the function accepts any number of trailing arguments.
// builtin_skriv formats its arguments as text and writes to stdout without a newline.
// builtin_skriv_linje is skriv followed by a newline (the most common output builtin).
// builtin_les_linje reads one line from stdin and returns it as a text value.
// builtin_type_of returns the runtime type name as a text string ("heltall", "tekst", etc.).
// builtin_lengde returns the number of elements in a list, map, or characters in a text.
// builtin_til_tekst converts any value to its text representation.
// builtin_til_heltall parses a text string or truncates a float to an integer.
// builtin_legg_til appends one element to the end of a list in place.
// builtin_sorter sorts a list in place; an optional comparator function may be provided.
// builtin_skjær returns a sub-list from start index to end index (exclusive).
// builtin_nøkler returns a list of all keys in a map.
// builtin_elementer returns a list of [key, value] pairs for a map.
// builtin_del_tekst splits a text string on a separator and returns a list.
// builtin_erstatt replaces all occurrences of a pattern with a replacement text.
// builtin_formater formats a text string with positional or named placeholders.
// builtin_json_parse deserializes a JSON text into Norscode values (maps, lists, primitives).
// builtin_json_stringify serializes a Norscode value tree to a JSON text string.
// builtin_assert raises a runtime error if its condition is false.

// Primitive flow:
// vm_dispatch op_call_builtin(id, argc):
//   builtin = builtin_registry[id]
//   args = vstack_pop(argc)
//   result = builtin_fn(args)
//   vstack_push(result)
// skriv("hei"): builtin_skriv_linje -> format "hei" -> write to stdout
// legg_til(liste, verdi): validate list type -> list.append(verdi) -> return null
// json_parse(tekst): parse JSON string -> build Norscode value tree -> return root

