// Semantic direction:
// vm_debugger instruments the VM execution loop to support interactive debugging.
// debug_attach connects a debugger to a running VM without restarting it.
// bp_set registers a breakpoint at bp_func / bp_offset or source bp_line.
// bp_condition is a Norscode expression evaluated before pausing; skips if false.
// bp_hit_count increments each time the breakpoint fires, regardless of condition.
// step_into_vm pauses at the next instruction, descending into called functions.
// step_over_vm pauses at the next instruction in the current frame, skipping calls.
// step_out_vm continues until the current frame returns, then pauses.
// inspect_frame reads frame_locals and frame_upvalues without modifying them.
// location_from_ip converts an instruction pointer to source_location_vm using the debug info.
// watch_expr evaluates watch_source in the current frame at each pause.
// vm_event_dbg is the notification sent to a connected IDE or REPL on every state change.
// on_pause fires when execution halts (breakpoint, step, or exception).
// on_exception_dbg fires before the VM unwinds a throw, giving a chance to inspect the state.

// Primitive flow:
// execution loop: at each instruction, check bp_set for current (func, offset)
//   bp_hit: bp_hit_count++ -> evaluate bp_condition -> if true: pause
//   step_mode active: pause after every instruction (step_into) or after frame depth unchanged (step_over)
// on pause: snapshot frame_locals + upvalues -> notify on_pause -> wait for resume command
// inspect: read val_repr for each frame_local -> format as key: type = value
// resume: dbg_running -> continue execution_loop

// This defines VM debugger support: conditional breakpoints, step modes,
// frame inspection, watch expressions, and debugger event notifications.

