// Semantic direction:
// module is the unit of compilation and encapsulation; each .no source file is one module.
// module_exports is the set of publicly visible symbols from this module.
// module_imports declares which symbols are needed from other modules.
// module_cache avoids loading the same module twice; cache_by_path is the primary key.
// module_resolver searches search_paths to find the file for an import_module_name.
// std_path is the standard library directory included in every project's search_paths.
// import_all imports every exported symbol from a module into the current namespace.
// qualified_name is the dot-separated reference to an imported symbol (std.tekst.del).
// cross_module_call resolves a function reference at call time using module_func_ref.
// resolve_callee looks up callee_func_id in callee_module's module_functions table.
// module_init runs the module's top-level initialization code once at load time.
// init_order performs a topological sort of imports to ensure dependencies initialize first.
// init_cycle_detect raises an error when two modules depend on each other at init time.
// hot_reload replaces a module's functions in place without restarting the VM.
// invalidate_jit_mod evicts all JIT-compiled code for the reloaded module.
// reload_callback is invoked after a successful hot_reload to update live references.
// link_imports patches all unresolved_import slots after all modules are loaded.
// circular_import is raised when import graph contains a dependency cycle.

// Primitive flow:
// load: import "std.tekst" -> module_resolver -> find file -> load_module
//   parse + compile -> module_functions + module_exports -> module_cache
//   link_imports: for each unresolved_import: resolve -> patch callee reference
// call: op_call on cross-module reference -> cross_module_dispatch
//   resolve_callee(module_func_ref) -> jump to function code
// init: init_order sort -> for each module: run_module_init if not init_done
// hot_reload: file changed -> reload_module -> replace_functions -> invalidate_jit_mod
//   live function refs updated -> reload_callback notified

// This defines the module system: loading, caching, import/export resolution,
// cross-module dispatch, initialization order, and hot reloading.

