// Semantic direction:
// basic_block_n is a maximal sequence of instructions with one entry and one exit.
// conditional_b emits a B.cond instruction; the fall_through path is the next basic block.
// loop_preheader_n is a block inserted before loop_header_n to hold loop-invariant hoisted code.
// switch_n with few cases emits a chain of comparisons; with many cases it uses a jump_table.
// jump_table is an array of branch target addresses; the switch value indexes into it.
// range_check_switch verifies the value is within [min, max] before the table lookup.
// exception_table maps instruction address ranges to landing_pad addresses.
// exc_try_range is the half-open interval [begin, end) of instructions covered by a try.
// exc_handler_ip is the address of the landing_pad for a matching exception type.
// landing_pad is the code that receives an in-flight exception and either handles or rethrows it.
// lp_cleanup marks a landing pad that always runs (like finally) regardless of exception type.
// unwind_info is the compact unwind / DWARF FDE used by the OS unwinder to find handlers.
// compact_unwind is the macOS-specific 32-bit encoding for common frame layouts.
// native_throw stores the exception value and type, then begins stack unwinding.
// find_handler_n walks the exception_table and call stack to find the nearest matching handler.
// run_cleanup_n executes finally blocks during unwinding before control reaches the handler.
// try_begin_n records the start address of a protected range in the exception_table.
// try_end_n closes the range; the handler address is resolved at link time via a label.

// Primitive flow:
// conditional branch: CMP reg1, reg2 → B.eq target (flag-based)
// switch: CMP value, #max_case → B.hi default → ADRP x1, jump_table@PAGE
//   ADD x1, x1, jump_table@PAGEOFF → LDR x0, [x1, value, LSL #3] → BR x0
// throw: native_throw(value, type) → exception_table search → find_handler
//   unwind: per-frame: run_cleanup (finally) → pop frame → check handler range
//   landing_pad reached: landing_pad_code runs → catch block or rethrow

// This defines native control flow: conditional branches, jump tables, switch,
// exception tables, landing pads, stack unwinding, and try/catch/finally.

