// Semantic direction:
// native_pipeline is the end-to-end compiler pass that takes Norscode source to a native binary.
// Each ps_* stage runs in sequence; early stages produce IR consumed by later stages.
// ps_parse: selfhost_parser or Python parser → typed AST.
// ps_typecheck: type inference + checking → typed IR with type annotations.
// ps_lower_ir: typed AST → SSA IR (three-address form with phi functions).
// ps_optimize: const fold, DCE, inlining, LICM → optimized SSA IR.
// ps_isel: BURS tiling → machine instructions with virtual registers.
// ps_regalloc: graph coloring → physical register assignment + spill code.
// ps_emit: machine instructions → assembly text (via aarch64_asm_gen) or object bytes.
// ps_link: object files + runtime library → executable binary.
// ps_debug_info: DWARF emission → attached to object files.
// lower_closure_n handles closures: captures moved to heap, closure struct allocated.
// lower_struct_n maps struct construction to rt_alloc + field stores.
// lower_list_n maps list literals to rt_list_new + rt_list_push calls.
// lower_map_n maps map literals to rt_map_new + rt_map_set calls.
// ssa_construction builds SSA form: phi placement + variable renaming pass.
// ssa_destroy converts out of SSA by inserting parallel copies at phi predecessors.
// backend_n selects the target_macos_arm64 or target_linux_x86 instruction set.
// emit_asm_n produces assembly text; assemble_n invokes clang to produce an object file.
// link_rt_n adds the norscode_rt object to the link step.
// nc_build_native is the CLI command: compile + link to a standalone executable.
// incremental_n checks dep_hash_n of each source file; skips compilation when cached_object is valid.

// Primitive flow:
// nc bygg --mål native fil.no:
//   ps_parse → AST
//   ps_typecheck → typed AST
//   ps_lower_ir → SSA IR
//   ps_optimize (if opt_level > 0)
//   ps_isel → machine instructions (virt regs)
//   ps_regalloc → physical regs + spills
//   ps_emit → assembly text (lower_func for each function)
//   assemble_n → .o object file
//   link_rt_n + link_objects → native binary
//   ps_debug_info → .dSYM (if debug_n)
// incremental: hash source → compare dep_hash → skip if object_valid

// This defines the full native compilation pipeline: SSA construction, lowering,
// optimization, instruction selection, register allocation, and link.

