// Semantic direction:
// std.ordbok wraps the native_map with ergonomic Norscode functions.
// ordbok_hent_eller returns a default value when the key is absent.
// ordbok_kart_verdier applies a function to each value and returns a new ordbok.
// ordbok_filtrer_o keeps only entries where the predicate returns true.
// ordbok_slå_sammen merges two maps; values from the second map overwrite the first on key clash.
// ordbok_oppdater is like slå_sammen but modifies the first map in place.
// ordbok_inverter swaps keys and values; raises if values are not unique.
// ordbok_grupper is liste_grupper_ved returning an ordbok instead of a list.
// std.path provides pure path manipulation without filesystem access.
// path_join combines components with the OS separator; handles absolute and relative components.
// path_normalisér resolves `.` and `..` without touching the filesystem.
// path_kanonisér resolves symlinks and returns the absolute path (requires filesystem access).
// path_komponenter splits a path into its directory and file name parts as a list.
// path_med_utvidelse replaces or adds the file extension.
// std.fil provides synchronous file I/O built on the OS file system calls.
// fil_les_linjer splits the file content on newlines and returns a list of strings.
// fil_les_bytes returns the raw file content as a liste of integers (one per byte).
// fil_legg_til appends content without truncating the existing file.
// fil_metadata returns size, modification time, and permissions.
// mappe_gå_gjennom recursively walks a directory tree, yielding paths.
// gjennomgang_dybde limits how deep the walk descends.
// gjennomgang_følg_lenker controls whether symbolic links are followed.
// current_dir and set_current_dir get and set the process working directory.

// Primitive flow:
// ordbok_slå_sammen(a, b): copy a → for each (k,v) in b: a[k] = v → return a
// path_join("src", "main.no"): "src" + "/" + "main.no" = "src/main.no"
// path_normalisér("a/../b/./c"): resolve .. and . → "b/c"
// fil_les_tekst("fil.no"): open → read_all → decode utf-8 → close → return tekst
// mappe_gå_gjennom("./src", dybde=∞): BFS/DFS → yield each file path

// This defines std.ordbok (map operations), std.path (pure path manipulation),
// and std.fil (synchronous file I/O and directory traversal).

