// Semantic direction:
// tidspunkt represents an absolute moment in time as seconds and nanoseconds since Unix epoch.
// ts_nå reads the wall clock; ts_mono_nå reads the monotonic clock for elapsed-time measurement.
// tidssone encodes a timezone as name and offset; tz_lokal reads the system timezone.
// dato represents a calendar date without time or timezone.
// dato_parse interprets a string using ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DD) or a custom format.
// dato_formater produces a string using strftime-style format codes (e.g. %d.%m.%Y).
// dato_legg_til adds a varighet (in days); dato_diff returns the signed number of days between two dates.
// klokkeslett is the time of day: hour, minute, second, nanosecond.
// dato_tid combines a date, time, and timezone into a fully specified moment.
// dt_til_ts converts to a Unix timestamp in the given timezone.
// dt_formater uses ISO 8601 by default; accepts custom format strings.
// varighet is a signed duration in seconds + nanoseconds (no calendar ambiguity).
// var_fra_dager converts days to seconds (86400 × days).
// var_mellom returns the elapsed varighet between two tidspunkts.
// tidtaker measures elapsed real time using ts_mono_nå.
// tt_elapsed returns the varighet since tt_start was called.
// sov suspends the current thread or task for a varighet.
// vent_til suspends until the wall clock reaches the given tidspunkt.

// Primitive flow:
// ts_nå(): syscall clock_gettime(CLOCK_REALTIME) → tidspunkt{sek, ns}
// dato_nå(): ts_nå() → UTC or local calendar decomposition → dato{år, måned, dag}
// var_mellom(t1, t2): t2.sek - t1.sek + (t2.ns - t1.ns)/1e9 → varighet
// dt_formater(dt, "%d.%m.%Y %H:%M"): map format codes to dt fields → concat string
// sov(varighet{sek=1, ns=500_000_000}): clock_nanosleep or kqueue timer → resume after 1.5s

// This defines the native std.tid module: timestamps, dates, times, timezones,
// duration arithmetic, formatting, parsing, and sleep/wait operations.

