// Semantic direction:
// std.kanal wraps the native channel for Norscode programs.
// kanal_ny creates a channel with a given kapasitet_k (0 = unbuffered).
// kanal_motta_eller returns a fallback value instead of blocking when the channel is empty.
// kanal_motta_alle drains all currently available values into a list without blocking.
// pub_sub implements a topic-based publish-subscribe pattern.
// abonnér registers a receiver on an emne; publisér sends to all current subscribers.
// emne_history keeps the last N messages for late-joining subscribers.
// signal_registrer hooks an OS signal to a Norscode handler function.
// avbrudd_kanal returns a channel that receives a value when SIGINT fires.
// std.logg provides structured logging to file, console, or remote sinks.
// logg_felt adds arbitrary key-value pairs to a log entry for structured output.
// beh_json_l formats each log entry as one line of JSON for log aggregators.
// beh_roter creates a rotating log file: after roter_størrelse bytes, a new file begins.
// beh_filter wraps a handler and drops entries below a minimum logg_nivå.
// beh_async_l buffers entries in a channel and writes on a background thread.
// beh_sende ships log entries to a remote endpoint (e.g. Loki, CloudWatch).
// std.feil provides a rich error type for the Norscode error handling model.
// feil_med_kontekst wraps an existing error with a human-readable context message.
// feil_lenke attaches the original feil_årsak for full error chain traversal.
// feil_er_type tests if an error's feil_type matches a given type name.
// feil_nedkast extracts the concrete error payload if the type matches.

// Primitive flow:
// kanal_ny(10): alloc ring_buffer(10) → return kanal handle
// publisér(emne, verdi): for each subscriber: kanal_send → wake receiver
// logg_info(logger, "Startet", {port: 8080}): build logg_oppføring → route to beh_json_l → write
// beh_roter: on write: if fil_størrelse > roter_størrelse: rotate → open new file
// feil_med_kontekst(io_feil, "Kunne ikke lese konfig"): feil{årsak=io_feil, kontekst="Kunne ikke..."}

// This defines std.kanal (channel wrappers), pub/sub, OS signal hooks,
// std.logg (structured logging with handlers), and std.feil (rich error types).

