// Semantic direction:
// stdlib_native bundles all native stdlib implementations into a single loadable library.
// std_bundle is the compiled shared library or static archive that ships with Norscode.
// std_verify checks the stdlib integrity using checksums against std_version_sl.
// std_load initializes the stdlib for the current process; it is called by rt_init.
// module_registry maps module names to their native implementations and loaded status.
// reg_lookup resolves a module name to its function table and symbol addresses.
// lazy_load defers loading a module until its first symbol is accessed.
// eager_load compiles and loads all std modules at startup for minimal first-call latency.
// bruk_stmt is the compiler representation of an import declaration.
// import_resolve maps the module name in bruk to a native module address.
// import_symbol resolves a specific exported function or value from a module.
// import_all_sl imports every exported symbol from a module into the current namespace.
// cmd_std_list prints all available standard library modules with a one-line summary.
// cmd_std_info prints the full module documentation and exported symbols.
// cmd_std_doc opens the module's documentation page in the browser or terminal pager.
// cmd_std_test runs the module's built-in test suite and reports pass/fail.
// cmd_std_deps shows which other modules a given module depends on.
// compat_check compares the current stdlib version against a required version range.
// compat_breaking reports API changes that require code updates in dependent programs.
// property_test generates random inputs (pt_runs iterations), runs the predicate, and shrinks pt_counterexample on failure.
// pt_generator is a function that produces a random value of a specific type.
// pt_shrink reduces a failing input to the smallest reproducing counterexample.

// Primitive flow:
// nc run app.no: parser sees `bruk std.json` → import_resolve("std.json") → load mod_json_sl
