// Semantic direction:
// json_api provides conventions for building REST APIs: resource routes, versioning, and standard response shapes.
// api_ressurs groups related endpoints: liste (GET /), hent (GET /:id), opprett (POST /), etc.
// innholdsforhandling inspects the Accept header and picks the best matching MIME type.
// forhandl returns a handler that dispatches to the appropriate renderer based on Accept.
// api_svar wraps the response in a standard envelope: {data, errors, meta, links}.
// jsonapi_format follows the JSON:API specification for resource objects and relationships.
// hal_format follows the HAL specification for hypermedia links.
// paginering adds page_number, page_size, total, and navigation links to list responses.
// cursor_paginering uses an opaque cursor instead of offset; safe for real-time data.
// sortering_api parses ?sort=felt,-annet into a list of (field, direction) pairs.
// filtrering_api parses ?filter[felt][gte]=10 into structured filter expressions.
// validering checks incoming request bodies against val_skjema before the handler runs.
// val_tilpasset accepts a user-supplied function for domain-specific validation logic.
// val_feil carries the field path and a human-readable message for each violation.
// api_feil maps common errors to standard HTTP status codes and JSON error bodies.
// http_422 is returned when the request is syntactically valid but semantically invalid.
// http_429 is returned when rate limiting fires; includes a Retry-After header.

// Primitive flow:
// GET /api/v1/brukere?sort=-navn&page=2&filter[aktiv]=true:
//   ruter matches → innholdsforhandling (Accept: application/json)
//   validering: params OK → filtrering_api: {aktiv: true} → sortering_api: [{navn, desc}]
//   paginering: page=2, size=20 → offset=20
//   handler: db.query(filter, sort, offset) → liste
//   api_svar: {data: [...], meta: {total: 83}, links: {neste: "?page=3", forrige: "?page=1"}}
//   → svar_json(svar, api_svar)

// This defines JSON API conventions, content negotiation, request validation,
// pagination, filtering, sorting, and standard error response formatting.

