// Semantic direction:
// tegner_2d is the 2D rendering context; tegner_begynn clears the frame and starts a new batch.
// kamera_2d defines the visible portion of the game world; zoom scales it; rotasjon_2d tilts it.
// kamera_til_verden converts a screen position to world coordinates for mouse picking.
// kamera_til_skjerm converts a world position to screen coordinates for UI elements.
// tekstur_last loads an image from disk and uploads it to the GPU as a texture.
// filter_nærmest gives sharp pixel-art style rendering; filter_lineær smoothly interpolates.
// sprite is a textured rectangle: a region of a tekstur with position, rotation, and scale.
// sprite_opprinnelse is the anchor point for rotation and scaling (default: center).
// sprite_ark (sprite sheet) packs many sprites into one tekstur to reduce draw calls.
// ark_hent_region returns the UV rectangle for one cell in the sprite sheet grid.
// animasjon_2d sequences through ark_ruter at anim_fps_2d; anim_loop_2d controls repetition.
// sprite_batch collects many sprite_draw calls and submits them in one GPU draw call.
// kart (tilemap) stores a grid of flis_id values; kart_lag allows multiple overlapping layers.
// flis_kollisjons marks tiles the physics engine should treat as solid.
// kart_verdens_til_flis converts a world coordinate to the tile row and column it occupies.
// farge_blend combines two colors using alpha compositing.

// Primitive flow:
// render frame: tegner_begynn → kamera sett opp → sprite_batch.begynn
//   kart_tegn(bakgrunn_lag) → for each synlig flis: batch.legg_til(sprite)
//   for each entitet med Sprite komponent: batch.legg_til(sprite)
//   sprite_batch.slutt → GPU draw call → swap buffers → tegner_slutt
// animation: anim_oppdater(delta_tid) → frame_idx = (elapsed / (1/fps)) as int
//   if frame_idx >= ruter.lengde: loop → reset or freeze

// This defines 2D rendering: camera, textures, sprites, sprite sheets, animations,
// sprite batching, and tilemap rendering with layered support.

