// Semantic direction:
// tegner_3d manages the 3D rendering pipeline using the GPU backend (Metal/Vulkan/wgpu).
// mesh is a 3D geometry: indexed triangles with per-vertex normals, UVs, and optional tangents.
// materiale defines how a surface looks; mat_shader selects the rendering algorithm.
// pbr_material implements Physically Based Rendering: metallic-roughness workflow.
// pbr_utregn_lys computes the lighting equation for a surface point given all active lights.
// shader_kompiler compiles GLSL/WGSL/Metal shader source to GPU bytecode.
// uniform_mat4 passes a 4×4 matrix to the shader (e.g. model-view-projection matrix).
// gjengivelse_kø collects render_objekt entries and sorts them for efficient GPU submission.
// gjengivelse_frustrumskutt discards objects outside the camera frustum before sending to GPU.
// gjengivelse_sorter orders objects: opaque front-to-back (minimize overdraw), transparent back-to-front.
// gjengivelsesmål is an offscreen render target; the result is a tekstur for post-processing.
// skybox renders a cube map as the background before all other geometry.
// bloom extracts bright areas and adds a glow effect in a post-processing pass.
// tone_mapping converts HDR values to LDR for display (Reinhard, ACES, etc.).
// fxaa (Fast Approximate Anti-Aliasing) smooths jagged edges in a single post-process pass.
// ssao (Screen Space Ambient Occlusion) approximates shadow in crevices using depth information.
// dybde_skarphet blurs objects outside the focus range for a cinematic depth-of-field effect.

// Primitive flow:
// frame: tegner_3d_begynn
//   gjengivelse_kø: collect synlig_3d nodes → frustrumskutt → sort
//   for each opaque render_objekt: bind shader → set uniforms (MVP matrix, mat props) → draw mesh
//   skybox_tegn (last, after opaques)
//   for each transparent render_objekt: back-to-front blend
//   gjengivelsesmål → etterbehandling (bloom → tone_mapping → fxaa)
//   swap → tegner_3d_slutt

// This defines the 3D rendering pipeline: mesh geometry, PBR materials, shaders
// with uniforms, render queuing with frustum culling, and post-processing effects.

